                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370612-name-1010" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1010" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1010" type="surname" value="ELEON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370612-name-1010" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH ELEON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Richard Eleon, who keeps the White Horse, in Little Britain. On the 9th of June, at half-past ten o'clock at night the prisoner came and asked for a lodging—he paid eightpence for it and went to bed—the next morning he came down at half-past eight o'clock with a large bundle-that caused my suspicions, and I sent after him-these sheets and bolster are mine—they were on the bed that night.</p>
